{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_albatross_ver01/data/sn86089566/00517176382/1908062801/0275.xml":{"full_text":"FROM TRtTBSDAY's DAILY.\nBRYAN WILL\nGET THERE.\nUNITED PRESS STAFF COR\nRESPONDENT SIZES UP\nTHE SITUATION.\nBryan\u2019s Friends Claim 750 In\n\u2022tructed Volea Out of the Total\nof 1,008 Delegate! Only\n672 Required.\nHy Lull'd pr\u00bb-*\u00bb\nDenver. Culo., June 25 Jacob\nWaldeck, staff correspondent at the\nUnited Press is reviewing the\ndemocratic outlook and says\nBryan s nomination is good as made\nand there never was a surer thing\nin politics. Bryan's friends count\non at least 750 of the I,oo^ dele\ngates with only 672 necessary to\nnominate. The friends of Governor\nJohnson and Judge Gray are still\nfighting. Johnson s headquarters\nare now open and he may be look*\ning to the 1912 convention. Former\nGovernor Douglas, of Mass A.\nTowne, Cornelius Pugsly of New\nYork, Prank Katzenbach of New\nJersey. John W. Korn, of Indiana,\nCongressman James of Kentucky.\nJudson Harmon of Ohio, and Gov.\nFolk of Mo., are the vice pres\nidential possibilities\nTWO LEADERS HUNG.\nShah's Troops Protecting The\nBritish Legation at Teheran.\nHv u\u00bb.h\u00abi pmi\nIxmdon, June 25.\u2014According to\na Teheran correspondent of the\nTimes, two nationalist leaders were\nhanged in the royal camp Wednes\nday. There is much anxiety regard\ning the other leaders not withstand\ning the Shahs promise to spare\ntheir lives. Troops guard all ap\nproarhes to the British legation\nwith orders to shoot fugitives seek\ning a sanctuary there.\nSHERMAN IS BETTER.\nSpecialist Summoned Tu See Him\nWired Not To Come.\nHl I\u2019Nllil P\u2019\nCleveland, June 25 Con\ngressman Sherman s condition his\nimproved His temperature. res\npiration and pulse are better and\nhe passed a comfortable night He\nis expected to leave tin hospital in\na week. Physicians have decided\nthat no operation is required now\nand the specialists who were sum\nmoned have been diiected not to\ncome.\nIN HONOR OF THE DEAD\nPresident Orders Flags Half Mast\ned At All Embassies And\nSalute Fired At All Posts\nFor Our Late Ex*\nPresident.\nm unit'd\nWashington. D. C June 25.\nIrders have been telegraphed\nthroughout the world to all govern\nment agencies abroad for a pmprr\nobservation of Ex President Cleve\nland s death. Flags will be kept\nat half mast at all the rmbi^ies\nand legations for thirty days and\na salute of 21 guns will be find at\nall army posts. All the warships\nwill tire guns every half hour on\nthe day of the funeral\nFILIPPINOS LIGHTING\nHill Tribesmen Kill Several Amer\nicans.\nH\u00ab U\u00bb lt'd PTtm\nManila. June 25.\u2014A telegram\nfrom the Isle of Negros annoum es\nthe murder of 11. Deverett. the\ngovernment forester, and T. R.\nWakeley a school teacher, also four\nFilippinos, by the Hill tribesmen\nibe party hail been missing for\nSix weeks.\nFIRST BALE\nOF COTTON\nSELLS AT AUCTION IN NEW\nYORK FOR THIRTY-FIVE\nCENTS A POUND.\nWas Raised in Houston County\nText\u00bb-Will Be Shipped at\nOnce to Europe. Proceeda\nGo to Charity.\nBy ['lilt'd erm*.\nNew York. June 25. \u2014The first\nbale of cotton of the season was\nsold on the steps of the -New York\ncotton exchange to A. G. Huledron\nand Company for thirty-five cents\nper pound or about three times its\nmarket value It was then im\nmediately sent to the Cunard docks\nand will be shipped on the steamer\nMauritania. This year's bale was\ngathered in Houston County Texas.\nEvery year there is great rivalry\nbetween counties to get the first\nbale to New York. In 1907 Hidal\ngo County was successful on June\n25, and tl. year when crop was\nlate. Brownsville, won on July 25.\nThe record is held by Galveston\nwith June Di. Tin* money from the\nsale always goes to charity.\nFALL OF SIXTY FEET.\nLee Harry's Skull Was Opened\nAnd He May Not Live.\nHv In it'd Pr*\u00ab\u00ab\nllallettNvilie, lex .June 23.\u2014Lee\nHarry, a young white Imy about lb\nyears old, whose home is in Yoakum,\nwm seriously injured almut 2 o'clock\nthis morning by being knocked oIT\na moving freight train while croM\ning the Mvac* River here It is\nsaid that Harry, in company with\ntwo or three oth\u00ab Imys of Yoakum,\nboarded the through freight which\nleft Yoakum after midnight going\ntoward Houston. I hey were dis\ncovered about four mile* west of\nhere ami the train was Ntopped and\nthey were pul off. but they evidently\ncliinlwd upon the train again when\nit started. It is supposed that Harry\nwas standing on the top of a box\ncar as the train started across the\nLavaca River bridge and he was\neither knocked off by the crosslwam\nof the bridge or slipped and fell off,\nf illing a distance of almut sixty feet\nto the crerk below. A deep gash\nfrom which the brain was oozing\nwas cut in his head. It is thought\nthat his head struck the edge of the\nbridge as he fell. Hr was found at\nthe water's edge unconscious. He\nwill Iw\u00bb taken I Yoakum today on\nthe regular passenger. Ihe attend\ning physician is unable to say\nwhether or not he will survive.\nCLEVELAND'S FUNERAL\nPresident Roosevelt Will Attend\nfhe Ceremonies To Be Ex\ntremely Simple.\nHy I'tol'vl Pm*\nPrinceton, June 25. President\nRoosevelt is expected to arrive at\nnoon tomorrow for the Cleveland\nfuneral all arrangements will then\nbe completed. i'he funeral will tn*\nextremely simple. Only invited per\nsons will be allowed on the grounds.\nThe town is filled with visitors to\npay their res|wcts but the body\nwill not lie in State. Mrs. Cleve\nland is (waring up well. Esther\nami Marion the oldest children will\narrive tonight.\nThe following pall bearers have\nbeen announced: Paul|Morton, E.\nC. Benedict, Dr. Henry Vandike,\nJohn Hibben, Prof. Andrew West,\nand President Finley of the New\nYork College. The funeral march\nwill be rop'd off and guarded by\n|milicp ami militia. Messages of\ncondolence are received from all\nparts of the world.\nTHE SHAH IS WARNED.\nBoth England And Russia May\nTake A Hand In Restoring\nOrder.\nby i DifeM PW\u00ab\nSt Petersburg. June 25 Russia\nand England have warned the Shah\nthat unless order is restored and\noutrages cease, he will l\u00bbe dethroned\nby the powers and his uncle. Prince\nZill will be made ruler.\nCONFESSES AN\nAWFUL MURDER\nYOUNG MAN FROM FORT\nWORTH KILLS HIS WIFE\nAT HOUSTON.\nTwo Negroes Taking A Trunk To\nDepot Drop II In Buf&lu Hur\non Where Body Of Dead\nWoman la Found.\nHy Unit'd\nHouston, Texas, June 25. C. B.\nj MeaJows, of Fort Worth, Texas,\nwas arrested here late yesterday\nafternoon, charged with the n.urd\ner of his wife. The woman's body\nwas found floating io a trunk in a\nnude condition in the bayou. It was\nplainly seen that she had been\nstrangled to death. The trunk was\nbeing taken from the wharf to the\nstation by two negroes to be sent\n|to Harrisburg, Texas, when they\naccidentally fell into the bayou\nwith the trunk. They were rescued\nand later the trunk was recovered\nwhen the horrible discovery was\nmade. Meadows was immediately\narrested and has confessed to the\ncrime.\nSHAHS TROOPS ACTIVE\nAre Ordered To Kill All Who Are\nEngaged In The Uprising.\nHy Cull'd PF'\u00bb\u00bb.\nTeheran, June2s. Shah's troops\nnow hold the town preventing a\nrevolt for the time being. The\nShah is acting arbitrariully and\nI has ordered the execution of all\n\u00a1those participating in the uprising\n'Hundreds are already jailed.\n(Throughout the country the refor\nmem are arousing the people and\nthe rebela are reported marching\nlon the city from the north. Tr<M>ps\nwill lie sent to meet them\nREPUBLICAN CHAIRMANSHIP.\n\n1 Post Master Genersl Myer Said To\nBe The Choice Of Both Taft\nAnd Roosevelt.\nBy UdIUM Pr\u00bb-M.\nOyster Bay. June 25. \u2014lt is now\nreported that Post Master General\nMeyer will be chairman of the\nRepublican National Committee.\nRoosevelt and Taft both are be\nlieved to favor him ami it may be\nannounced next Saturday\nA LADY BADLY HURT.\nMrs. Ida Seegle Has Her Foot Cut\nOff While Crossing Railroad\nTrack.\nBy U ail'd Prr\u00bb\u00bb\n.San Antonio, Tex., June 25.-\nWhil? crossing the railroad track\nhere this morning Mrs. Ida Seegle.\nwife of well known merchant, was\nstruck by a switch engine. Her\nright foot was cut off and she was\nalso badly bruised about the\nbody.\nRAIL ROAD TIME TABLE.\nNATIONAL RAILROAD OF MRXIOO.\nThrough fast train for Mexico\nCity leaves I AG. N station at\n4:36 p. in. Arrives from Mexico\nCitv at 7 a. in. Standard time.\nfhe local Saltillo train leaves\nTexas Mexican station at 21 a. m\nArrives Iron Saltillo al 5 I\u00bb; p. m.\nStandard time.\nTKXAS MEXICAN.\nLeaves for Corpus Christi at 9:U\na. m.\nArrives from Corpus Christi at\n4 ml p. m. Standard time\nI INTERNATIONAL A HERAT NORTHERN\nThrough fast train for St. Ix>uis\nI leaves at 7 311 a. in. and arrives at\n\u00cd 4 35 p. m.\n1. A \u00abI. N. NIGHT TBAIN.\nI waves at 7 30 p. in. and arrives\nat 7 30 a m.\n810 GRANDE A RAGLE PASS.\nTrain No. 1 leaves I.a redo daily\nexcept Sunday at a. in Arrive at\nCannel 9 3U a. tn. Arrive at Minera\nat 10. a. m.\nTrain No 2 leave* Minera daile\nexcept Sunday at 11 a. m. Leavy\nCannel Ipm Arrive at Laredo\np m\nSPANISH STEAMER WRECKED\nGoes On The Rocks Off Ximida\nAnd Sunk Within A Few\nMinutes\nHy Uuited PfwM.\nMadrid. June 25.\u2014 Ilie Spanish\nsteamer La Riche struck on the\nrocks off Xi miela, where the steamer\nCardinal Cisneros and many others\nhave been loft and sank within a\ntew minutes Ihe Bra was very\nrough at the t ine. There are con\nflicting reports. Some state about\none hundred terso ns were drowned.\nOne report from Coruna says all\nwere saved. The La Riche had\ncalled at Cadiz to embark passeng\ners from Argentina for northern\nporta. She was bound for Muros.\nHer crew numbered .\u2019>3, and its\nvariously given, that from 7.\u00bb to mu\npassengers were aboard.\nA Grand Family Medicine\n\u2018\u2022lt gives me pleasure to speak a\ngood word for Electric Bitters,\u201d\nwrites Mr. Frank Conlan of No.\